# Docs link format: Markdown links only

In `apps/docs/content/**/*.md`, always use standard Markdown links:

- Use `[label](./relative-path.md)` for internal links
- Use `[label](#heading-anchor)` for section links
- Use full `https://...` URLs for external links

Do not use Obsidian wiki-link syntax (`[[...]]`).

## Gotcha

Quartz deploys and GitHub rendering expect plain Markdown link syntax. Wiki-links can render inconsistently outside Obsidian and cause broken navigation after deployment.

## Quick examples

- Good: `[Feature Catalog](./feature-catalog.md)`
- Good: `[Permissions](../permissions.md#permission-precedence-highest-to-lowest)`
- Bad: `[[./feature-catalog.md|Feature Catalog]]`
- Bad: `[[Permissions]]`
